<codeline><highlight class="normal">###<sp/>Build</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">libembroidery<sp/>and<sp/>EmbroiderModder<sp/>2<sp/>use<sp/>CMake<sp/>builds</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">so<sp/>if<sp/>you<sp/>are<sp/>building<sp/>the<sp/>project<sp/>to<sp/>use<sp/>as<sp/>a<sp/>library<sp/>we<sp/>recommend</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">you<sp/>run:</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">```sh</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">git<sp/>clone<sp/>https://github.com/Embroidermodder/libembroidery</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">cd<sp/>libembroidery</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">cmake<sp/>.</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">cmake<sp/>--build<sp/>.</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">cmake<sp/>--install<sp/>.</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">```</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">This<sp/>builds<sp/>both<sp/>the<sp/>static<sp/>and<sp/>shared<sp/>versions<sp/>of<sp/>the<sp/>library<sp/>as<sp/>well</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">as<sp/>the<sp/>command<sp/>line<sp/>program<sp/>`embroider`.</highlight></codeline>
